# Pricing-sync rule

## The rule

Foundation Founder pricing on this lander MUST stay in lockstep with the parent brand at `slatepress.co`. The two pages reference the same product (Foundation tier) and the same Founder cohort ceiling (50 spots). If the numbers drift between the two pages, prospects on a sales call comparing both pages catch the discrepancy and the trust hit is immediate.

## Sister repos under the same pricing scope

- `slatepress.co` (repo: `slatepress-site`) - the parent brand reference
- `plumbingslatepress.com` (this repo)
- Any future vertical-brand lander that also publishes a Foundation pricing card (`hvacslatepress.com`, `electricianslatepress.com`, `roofingslatepress.com`, etc.) once they graduate from splash-tier

If pricing changes on one page, the same change MUST be made on the others in the same session.

## Why this exists

On 2026-05-09 Anthony caught the two live pages drifting apart - slatepress.co was showing `$3,500` setup while plumbingslatepress.com was showing `$4,999`. Cross-page drift = customer-trust hit during sales calls + sales-conversation friction.

The fix: synced to `$4,999` in slatepress.co v26 commit `b393ca0`.

## Current Foundation pricing (verify on every edit)

- **Founder #1-50**: `$4,999` setup + `$269/mo`, grandfathered for life. Closes hard at #50.
- **Standard #51+**: `$8,999` setup + `$499/mo`.

## What to do when editing pricing on index.html

1. Before committing the pricing change on this repo, surface a reminder in the response that the same change is needed on `slatepress-site` (and any other live vertical landers that have pricing cards).
2. Pause for Anthony's confirmation that he wants to ship the cross-repo change too.
3. On confirmation, create matching feature branches on both repos, make the same edit on each, commit and push both, surface both preview URLs.
4. Anthony reviews both previews; merge both to main in the same session.

This rule applies to every pricing edit, no exceptions. The cleanest tell that this rule fired correctly: every pricing-change commit on this repo gets a sibling commit on slatepress-site within the same hour.
